# Exercise 2: E-commerce Platform Search Function

## 1. Understand Asymptotic Notation

### Big O Notation

Big O notation measures the efficiency of an algorithm as the input size grows.

Examples:

* O(1) – Constant
* O(log n) – Logarithmic
* O(n) – Linear
* O(n²) – Quadratic

### Search Cases

* **Best Case:** Item found immediately.
* **Average Case:** Item found in the middle.
* **Worst Case:** Item found at the end or not found.

---

## 2. Setup

```java
class Product {

    int productId;
    String productName;
    String category;

    Product(int id,String name,String category){
        this.productId=id;
        this.productName=name;
        this.category=category;
    }
}
```

---

## 3. Implementation

### Linear Search

```java
public static int linearSearch(Product arr[], String key){

    for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){

        if(arr[i].productName.equals(key))
            return i;
    }

    return -1;
}
```

### Binary Search

```java
public static int binarySearch(Product arr[], String key){

    int low=0;
    int high=arr.length-1;

    while(low<=high){

        int mid=(low+high)/2;

        int compare=arr[mid].productName.compareTo(key);

        if(compare==0)
            return mid;

        else if(compare<0)
            low=mid+1;

        else
            high=mid-1;
    }

    return -1;
}
```

---

## 4. Analysis

| Algorithm     | Time Complexity |
| ------------- | --------------- |
| Linear Search | O(n)            |
| Binary Search | O(log n)        |

### Which is Better?

Binary Search is better because it searches much faster for large sorted datasets.

